Hi Martin and Bill,

I understand your point. You realized you need a well defined
(general) language, and Aldor is it's implementation. This is much
better than Maple/Mathematica, I agree.

I am just addressing the technological point of view - you have a nice
language, tuned to the purpose of the CAS. This is certainly one way
to go.

There is certainly another way to go however, and that is the way I
took - don't reinvent some language, just take already working
language with a specification and a working (open source)
implementation. And a large userbase.

I think those are quite philosophical questions and it's not clear
which approach is better. So you just need to make some decision, and
I did one (with good arguments), you did another (with good
arguments).

Ondrej


