I suspect that arguments about typed language  in CAS may be more
convincing by studying cases where the type system does add value,
greatly help solve problems that are much more difficult to tackle
with a weakly typed language.  Otherwise, I suspect we'll get lost in
"computer scientists" discussions about advanced type systems.

-- Gaby, the devil advocate





